- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is also likely as the paper uses a discrete model to simulate pedestrian dynamics. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is another possible category as the paper deals with human behavior in pedestrian flow scenarios. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is a possible category as the model manages the dynamics of simulated group members with an adaptive mechanism. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also a possible category as the paper uses a simulation model to study pedestrian flow.
